keyValuePair.Value: Nothing seemed to go right for your team today. What was the problem?
You never really looked like scoring today and it ended up as a pretty emphatic defeat. What do you put the poor performance down to?
We just didn't cope defensively.

However good %1s were, I definitely think we can be better defensively than we were today. We were disorganised and didn't communicate. We just have to work even harder at being a solid unit and that means putting in the effort on the training pitch. The boys are as desperate to do well as I am, I promise you.
We were second best. It's as simple as that.

I think you have to give credit to the opposition today. %1s had a game plan and we couldn't find a way to deal with it. My boys were up against some very good players today and they'll have to learn a few lessons if we're going to compete at this level.

I think you have to give credit to the opposition today. %1s had a game plan and we couldn't find a way to deal with it. My boys were up against some very good players today and they'll have to learn a few lessons if we're going to compete at this level.
We let ourselves get bullied.

We had problems all over the pitch. I'd say we let ourselves get bullied out of the game, to be honest. We weren't brave enough to get men forward and make chances and we didn't work hard enough to win the ball back after our attacks broke down. Technically and physically, the lads have to give us more.
%1s were the better team today, weren't they? And that last goal sealed it?
You had good moments in the game and there were times when it looked like you might get back into it. But then that last %1s goal finished you off, didn't? Was that the key moment?
We did some good things in the game.

%1s are a very good side but, even so, for a lot of the game, I thought we could get something out of it. We had good spells but just didn't make them count. And then the last goal killed us. We did our best, but today our best wasn't good enough.
We competed well but %1s scored at a key time.

Look, of course none of us is happy about conceding that last goal, but I can't really be too critical of the boys about that defeat. They battled hard against a very good %1s side. Our problem was we didn't create enough in the final third. We never put them under enough pressure.
We paid for not giving ourselves something to hang onto.

We definitely had our moments. We created decent chances on the break but we didn't put any of them away. I'm disappointed, to be honest. We weren't good enough in either box. If we'd got a goal, it would have given us something to defend, something to fight for. Things could have been very different today.
It was quite a heavy defeat today. Could your team have done more?
There were times in the second half when it looked like you might get back into it. You even got that goal towards full-time. But was it a case of too little too late?
Were beaten by the better team on the day.
I don't think I could have asked for much more from the lads, to be honest. We worked hard and created opportunities but we let ourselves down defensively. %1s were just better than us on the day.
The scoreline flattered %1s.

Maybe I didn't realise just good %1s were defensively before today. The lads worked hard and did what they could. We definitely had our moments in the game but we couldn't create anything clear-cut before that late goal. It was tough on us. We were better than the scoreline suggests.
We got taught a bit of a lesson, didn't we?

We really paid for our defensive mistakes today. I know the lads got put under a lot of pressure but we never looked like getting on top of the opposition. We have to recognise how much work we have to do if we want to compete against the very best teams.
Were you worried that your team wasn't able to get back into the game even though there was plenty of time left?
%1s got what turned out to be the winner before half-time. There was plenty left in the game but you couldn't make a breakthrough. What was missing from the performance today?
It was a decent performance but a disappointing result.

I don't think we did a lot wrong today. I was pleased with the team's attitude and their work-rate. Yes, the result was disappointing, but I saw plenty of good things to take forward from the performance.

I don't think we did a lot wrong today. I was pleased with the team's attitude and their work-rate. Yes, the result was disappointing, but I saw plenty of good things to take forward from the performance.
It was one of those days us. Nothing went our way.

We just couldn't get back on terms, but I thought the boys did everything they could except get the goal we needed. We had chances, I guess, but nothing clear-cut. The lads certainly put the effort in but maybe it was just one of those days.

We just couldn't get back on terms, but I thought the boys did everything they could except get the goal we needed. We had chances, I guess, but nothing clear-cut. The lads certainly put the effort in but maybe it was just one of those days.
One defensive mistake can cost a team the game.

I don't want to be too harsh on the boys, but we have to wake up to the fact that it only takes one mistake to lose your team the game. That's what happened today. That first-half goal cost us, didn't it? We couldn't get back in it second half.

I don't want to be too harsh on the boys, but we have to wake up to the fact that it only takes one mistake to lose your team the game. That's what happened today. That first-half goal cost us, didn't it? We couldn't get back in it second half.
Why weren't your team able to make more of an impact in the second half?
A frustrating defeat for you. Once you went behind, you never really looked able to get back in the game. What was the problem today?
We just didn't take our chances

It's hard to take. I thought the lads played with great spirit and took the game to the opposition. The problem was that, for all our good approach play, we couldn't take advantage of any of the opportunities we created.

It's hard to take. I thought the lads played with great spirit and took the game to the opposition. The problem was that, for all our good approach play, we couldn't take advantage of any of the opportunities we created.
We win together and we lose together.

I don't think it's fair to put the blame on any one individual player. Yes, we conceded, but I thought we defended well for most of the game. And we had our moments going forwards. We weren't perfect but, on another day, we might have got a couple of goals and beaten %1s here. Let's focus on the positives we can take away from this.
We took too long to get into the game.

We've talked about how we start games before. I think the lads should know by now that the first few minutes is the time to really go for it. Before the opposition have had time to settle. Instead, today, we lost the initiative and conceded the decisive goal. That changed the whole game. We need to be the team that's first out of the blocks.
It must be frustrating to concede so late in the game. What happened?
There wasn't much in the game and it seemed like it would finish all square. But you conceded a late goal and lost. What happened? And what could your team have done better?
Going forward we did everything we could.

I thought we looked very dangerous for most of the game. Some of our attacking play was excellent and we probably deserved a draw. Sometimes it's down to who gets a lucky break. Today that wasn't us. It was our opponents.
It wasn't down to any lack of effort, that's for sure.

Of course the important thing is to win. That's our job. But today I was pleased with what I saw from most of our players. They worked hard from start to finish. %1s were strong all over the pitch but I thought our lads deserved better than to lose the game like that.

Of course the important thing is to win. That's our job. But today I was pleased with what I saw from most of our players. They worked hard from start to finish. %1s were strong all over the pitch but I thought our lads deserved better than to lose the game like that.
We have to be able to trust each other.

I want to trust my players. And I want them to be able to trust each other. They're talented footballers. But it always seems as if there'll be a moment when they switch off. That's what happened here. One lapse in concentration right at the end cost us the game today.

I want to trust my players. And I want them to be able to trust each other. They're talented footballers. But it always seems as if there'll be a moment when they switch off. That's what happened here. One lapse in concentration right at the end cost us the game today.
A costly defeat. What was to blame?
By the time you scored the last goal of the game, it was only a consolation. The match had already been lost. What went wrong?
Let's focus on how to improve.

Getting beaten by a team as good as %1s, I don't think it helps to jump up and down and look for somebody to blame. We have to look at what we did well and not just over-analyse where we went wrong. The important thing is to identify where and how we have to improve.

Getting beaten by a team as good as %1s, I don't think it helps to jump up and down and look for somebody to blame. We have to look at what we did well and not just over-analyse where we went wrong. The important thing is to identify where and how we have to improve.
I thought we deserved something from the game.

You want your players to get numbers forward and score and we did that. It just wasn't enough. It's a team game and, collectively, we just weren't good enough when we were out of possession. We got punished for every mistake.
Individual players have to take responsibility.

After today's result, I don't want to over-analyse our team performance. But, on this showing, it's clear every single player needs to take more responsibility. Each individual needs to analyse the weaknesses in his own game and work out how to fix things without always relying on somebody else to help him out.
A disappointing result, wasn't it? What was missing in today's performance?
You scored the last goal but it was no more than a consolation. The game had already been lost: a %1s-goal defeat in the end. What was wrong? What was missing from the team's performance today?
I can't fault the lads for attitude.

There were some good performances out there, despite the scoreline being disappointing. Nobody went missing, nobody shirked responsibility. I think the lads did what they could up against a very good %1s team.

There were some good performances out there, despite the scoreline being disappointing. Nobody went missing, nobody shirked responsibility. I think the lads did what they could up against a very good %1s team.
The lads never let their heads drop.

We got the last goal of the game and that shows you the lads weren't hiding. They weren't out there feeling sorry for themselves. But today they were second best against a very good team. I give them plenty of credit for not letting their heads drop, though.
There'll be some harsh words in the dressing room.

That was disappointing. We conceded a couple of very soft goals. But I'm not going to stand here and criticise my players in public. I hope they don't need me to tell them anyway. Today just wasn't good enough. We have to improve.
A very disappointing defeat. How do you explain what happened today?
Yes, you got a late goal, but the game was already lost, wasn't it? Where do you begin to explain such a disheartening performance?
We weren't as bad as the scoreline suggests.

I know that looks like a really bad defeat but I'm not so disappointed with the performance. Good as %1s were, I thought we kept trying to play even though nothing went our way. I think you have to say it was just a bad day at the office.

I know that looks like a really bad defeat but I'm not so disappointed with the performance. Good as %1s were, I thought we kept trying to play even though nothing went our way. I think you have to say it was just a bad day at the office.
We deserved better than that scoreline.

I can't be too harsh on the boys after that. I think we worked really hard to try and get back into the game. Our late goal shows we kept going. Nobody let his head drop. But it wasn't to be. We were up against a very well-organised team line today and nothing went our way.
We have to defend as a team.

Look, I believe in our players and we work hard with them during the week in training. But you saw what happened to us defensively today. Concentration? Self-belief? I don't what we're missing but it costs us in games like today. The lads need to be better. Our coaching staff can't help them once the match kicks off.
What went wrong today? Who do you blame?
You got a goal back but then couldn't ever get control of the game. It ended in quite a convincing defeat. Who's to blame for you coming up short?
Sometimes you have to credit your opponent.

We're all disappointed with the result. But sometimes you have to admit the other team was better on the day. %1s are as good as anyone around at the moment. We kept going but we never looked like being good enough to take something out of the game.
It's hard to defend when you're chasing the game.

I've got some sympathy for my players, given the way things unfolded. It's never easy when you're behind and having to chase the game. We committed men forward and that made it difficult for us whenever we lost the ball. I think that scoreline was harsh on us.
Players have to remember what their jobs are.

Sometimes effort on its own isn't enough. Definitely against better sides. We put a plan in place but it'll never work unless every single player looks after his own job. Otherwise we'll just get picked off by a half-decent team. Which is exactly what happened today.
How do you explain today's defeat? What did your team miss today?
You scored those late goals today but it never looked like being enough. It was a bad result. Was it a bad performance, too?
Let's not panic. We'll learn from today.

The players won't need me to point out the individual mistakes which let us down against %1s today. But I don't want to throw teacups around in the dressing room. Our job now has to be to look at the game and work out how we can improve.

The players won't need me to point out the individual mistakes which let us down against %1s today. But I don't want to throw teacups around in the dressing room. Our job now has to be to look at the game and work out how we can improve.
The players showed a bit of character, despite the defeat.

It would have been easy for the lads to let their heads drop. %1s are a decent side, especially once they get in front in a game. But I thought our lads played with a bit of pride, scored their goals, and probably deserved better than the scoreline suggests.

It would have been easy for the lads to let their heads drop. %1s are a decent side, especially once they get in front in a game. But I thought our lads played with a bit of pride, scored their goals, and probably deserved better than the scoreline suggests.
We lost our shape whenever we lost possession.

Of course the lads were up against some very good players, but it was individual errors that let us down today. If you manage to get goals at one end, you need to make sure you don't concede at the other. But we didn't stick to our jobs out of possession and switched off at vital times. That lack of discipline has probably cost us the game.
Why didn't your team start the game as well as you finished it?
You got those late goals but a slow start had already put the game too far out of reach. What lessons can your players learn from this defeat?
We should have applied early pressure.

My players have got plenty of quality, I know that. They work hard, too. But it took too long for them to get started today and so our goals came too late. They need to believe more in themselves and seize the initiative earlier in games. I'm sure they'll learn from this.
I didn't see anyone giving up out there.

I genuinely think the lads deserved to get something out of the game. They covered every blade of grass and never stopped trying. Nobody went missing. They can be proud of themselves despite %1s getting the result. There's definitely a decent spirit in this team.

I genuinely think the lads deserved to get something out of the game. They covered every blade of grass and never stopped trying. Nobody went missing. They can be proud of themselves despite %1s getting the result. There's definitely a decent spirit in this team.
We need to take charge in games.

I think we looked like a team that was waiting for things to happen instead of making them happen. To give ourselves a chance to win games like today's, we have to be more aggressive and make opponents worry about us rather than us worrying so much about them.
You are probably wondering how you didn't manage to get an equaliser in the second half?

Well, it was entertaining for the neutral. But it must have been frustrating for you. Such a tight game in the end. Did you expect the equaliser to come eventually second half? Or did you always suspect your boys would come up short?
We need a bit more quality.

I don't like to criticise my players when I see them working as hard as they did today. I guess we just gave ourselves too much to do in the end. We have to find a bit more quality if we're going to get something out of games like that.
Maybe it wasn't our day.

I can't fault the boys for effort in that second half. We were chasing the game and I thought we did enough to get something out of it. Sometimes, though, you just have to accept that it wasn't your day.
We gave ourselves too much to do.

I thought we deserved something from the game but I guess it's our own fault. We gave ourselves too much to do in the first place, and then didn't create the clear-cut chance to equalise in that second half.
You must have thought you'd get something from the game. Why did your team come up short?
It was a pretty tight game and you were just a goal down at half-time. Were you very frustrated not to find a way to get something out of the game in the second half?
We can't waste time feeling sorry for ourselves.

I want my lads to show that they can all be leaders. I don't want to see fingers being pointed when we concede a goal. I don't want to see heads go down when things don't go our way. I know we can be better. We'll be working hard on things in training this week.
We were good. But %1s were better.

I thought we competed well today. We were quick to the second ball after half-time and took the game to the opposition. It just wasn't enough in the end. That's down to %1s's quality, though, rather any lack of effort from my lads.
We have to take our chances.

The team did okay second half. I thought we had the better of it for long periods. But we needed to take our chances when we were on top and, for whatever reason, we didn't do that today. That's why we lost. Sometimes football's as simple as that.
After getting that late goal back, did you expect your team to find an equaliser to rescue the game?
When you got that late goal back you must have been hoping for one more to rescue a point from the game. Were you disappointed your team couldn't find that little bit extra?
We just couldn't get on the end of the chances we made.

I was pleased with the energy and commitment of my players. But when we needed something special from one of them to get us a draw, it wasn't there. We had chances to get something out of the game but it never happened. Sometimes you don't get the luck, do you?

I was pleased with the energy and commitment of my players. But when we needed something special from one of them to get us a draw, it wasn't there. We had chances to get something out of the game but it never happened. Sometimes you don't get the luck, do you?
We were always chasing the game.

We were up against a good %1s team. It always takes more energy when you're chasing a game than when you're protecting a lead. I think that's why we got one goal back but just couldn't find an equaliser. The boys were shattered by the end.
We let ourselves get overrun.

We were playing a good team today but I thought we gave them far too much respect. We were slow reacting to situations and they took advantage. In the end, those moments of hesitancy were what cost us the game. We have to be braver against the best teams.
